column2: much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans
column4: and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans
column6: and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words
column7: if youâ€™re waiting for them to make an apology

column9: men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please

column12: do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it.

column1: and then today. today i finally got myself to work out again. i ate mostly healthy and when i told myself i could just work out tomorrow
column2: i decided i needed to get on it and work out today. and i did. and it felt great.

tonight would be the night i fell
into the dark under a spell
many saw the plans he had for me
but none would stop the tyranny
so down and under the water i went
a dark tale birthed on ""all hallows eve""
as a rose petal falls to the ground
but wait! it is there that i should see
hope rising up as the sun in the east
for even aurora would awake from her sleep
as ariel died for she was not meant for the sea
so long as legends shine there is hope
though he took me with no consent to note
in the silence i hear a meak voice speak
for i know the plans i have for you
so sing out sweet rose and let it arise
upward to heaven and into the sky. .

column1: being a survivor of childhood sexual abuse has been 24 years of blank anger
column3: and terror i never knew how to explain. my brain erased my childhood for so long and one day
column4: it just decided to give it back. and at first

column1: but there is one thing i realize through all the memories
column3: the weird creepy things iâ€™d do and say... and itâ€™s not shame anymore. itâ€™s pride.

column1: i am haunted by the memories my brain guarded me from for decades in order to survive. i almost died several times since and iâ€™d be lying if i said that at the time
column2: i was disappointed each time i didnâ€™t. but i am strong. i am empathetic. i am devoted to aid. i am devoted to compassion.

column1: yes i remember the humiliation. i remember the family members who knew and hid it from my parents. i remember never feeling safe. i remember making up friends and games to distract my mind from reality. i remember being told that if i said anything
i remember feeling so different than every other child. so distant from kids
i remember hearing kids laugh upstairs in the house (when their were none) and when that happened
column4: and hide. i remember telling myself it was a game with kids... but now i remember that i really knew what was going to happen if i didnâ€™t... so i wanted to play upstairs instead. i remember the random big gifts out of nowhere that made me so

column1: i remember thinking that being so sick (unknowingly type 1 diabetic) was all my fault. that if i said anything to anyone
column2: something would happen to my sister (my mom was having a hard pregnancy) and i remember thinking â€œiâ€™m so tired and just want to sleep foreverâ€ at 7. i remember planning to run away once i made sure my baby sister was here and my mom was okay.

column1: i remember the things it took away from me but in that
column2: i now realize what it gave me. it gave me the power to stand strong one day
column3: to say to other women â€œi believe you.â€ it gave me the power to say â€œyou are not what your attacker made you feelâ€.

column1: 266389;instagram;2018-10-31 00:50:16;TRUE;;"repost from @life_after_rape_and_suicide - (lanjutan dari catatan 1) aku merasakan sakit dibawah sana. sangat sakit. aku masih melihat darah mengalir dikaki ku. tuhan
column2: mengapa tidak engkau ambil saja aku?

column1: aku menjalani malam yang panjang itu dengan menangis

column2: aku merasa diri ku berbeda. aku tidak keluar dari tempat tidurku sampai tob pergi. aku tidak mau melihatnya.

column3: tuhan. mengapa sakit sekali? aku menangis sepanjang hari. sore hari orangtua dan saudara lainnya telah pulang dari pesta
column4: begitu juga dengan tob. rumah sangat ramai saat itu. aku ingin sekali bercerita pada ibu. ingin aku menghambur ke pelukan ibu dan menangis. ingin aku dipeluk oleh ibu. aku ingin ayah mengusir tob.

column2: tidak sedikitpun dia bertanya bagaimana aku. aku pun pergi menjauh dari keramaian itu.
aku melihat tob dengan amarah yang membara. sementara dia bertingkah seolah-olah tidak ada yang terjadi. oh tuhan
column4: mengapa tidak engkau panggil dia? aku sering melamun

column2: aku ngotot untuk tidur bersama ibu. tetapi ibu memarahiku karena dianggap cengeng. aku kembali pada tempat tidur itu dengan perasaan yang tak tergambarkan. ibu. seandainya ibu tau

column7: if you have been trained not to bother people by saying help. if you are considered to be out of line when you speak up in a meeting
column8: are not admitted into an institution of power
column9: are subject to irrelevant criticism whose subtext is that women should not be here or heard.

column5: and an underclass of the voiceless.

column1: 266718;instagram;2018-10-30 19:29:52;FALSE;"i am looking at chocolate bars to purchase for the trick or treaters and a man walks down the grocery isle staring at me. i instantly feel my body stiffen. the man walks past me and stops 5 steps to my left and stares at the shelves

this is a man in his 50s who is making me feel like i am standing naked in the middle of a big box store and he is staring at each curve of my body. this is violation. i act casual looking at these stupid fucking chocolate bars telling the man to go fuck himself in my head. i can't make a decision
column2: he's ""casually"" inching closer to me/ the bars i'm looking at. he didn't walk down this isle to purchase goods
column3: he walked down here to breathe in my scent. this is fucking predatory shit. suddenly my body takes me to the complete opposite end of the store while looking over my shoulder. and stand looking at household objects for five minutes hoping i can safely go back to get that fucking chocolate.

column1: women should never have to feel this way - but we often do. nobody should ever feel unsafe in a store
column3: living their life. i'm so fucking sick of feeling this way and hearing others stories. why do some men do this?

column1: some days women's rights issues make me feel empowered to work harder and to be the change... some days it makes me feel like a bag of shit.
fuck. the. patriarchy & fuck people that make other humans feel less than.

column1: 266801;instagram;2018-10-30 18:38:34;FALSE;"many of you have seen the beautiful and powerful portrait that @shanawilsonartist painted of dr. christine blasey ford in the wake of the #kavanaugh confirmation hearings. we reached out to her to gather her thoughts on the time we are living in and her inspiration for this portrait.

column2: this is her art. thank you so much for your courage to speak out about your experience
column3: and we hope that this piece inspires others to do the same. your story is the most powerful thing you can share with the world
column4: and teaching the next generation about our experiences can help drive actual systemic change.

column1: we should not consider ourselves lucky for the near-misses or the ""light"" aggression we face daily as women; we should not live in fear or constant states of defense. we have a right to feel safe and to be believed when we have been hurt. we are here with you
column2: and thank you for sharing your stories and art with us and the world. #ibelievethem .

column1: 266802;instagram;2018-10-30 18:39:27;FALSE;"i was assaulted coming back from senegal
column2: and the experience has shaken up my world a bit. i've been writing extensively about this experience on my private channels
column3: but the most i'll say about it at this point is that talking about it helps. self-care and activity help. allowing myself the space to process it however i need is paramount. this time in the #metoo era has a lot of us experience something very similar in heartbreak and challenge. reach out to me if you need it. start a conversation about it. let's work together to make our spaces safer.

column1: i've been spending time in beautiful parts of spain and france with my partner going through it but also enjoying the amazing experience of traveling mountain towns and countrysides in love. this trip is a bit different from what we had both imagined before the assault
i'm grateful for the support and kindness i've been offered. some people i haven't yet responded to because my heart is still heavy and i need to recuperate
column2: but know that i'm embracing this newness and holding your offerings close. i'm finding my badass. i'm reconnecting to my strong.
this changes things but i'm developing something important from this.

column1: 266896;instagram;2018-10-30 16:57:58;FALSE;"the past 10 days have been exhausting for me. i'm in the middle of a 2 week straight working and it is just tiring. because i've been so tired
column2: i couldn't let feelings that i have stay buried. i did the brave thing and bore my soul to my boyfriend. it was scary as f***
column3: but we are better off for it. in the beginning of our relationship
column4: he ""asked"" me something but really it was he was going to do something and i had no say in the matter. as this event is getting closer
column5: my anxiety about it is increasing. it was important to me to make it clear how much his disregard for my feelings about this affected me. once i made it clear
column6: he apologized for his actions and even though the event is still going to happen
column7: i feel like i'm going to be able to get through this. and he also promised me that once this is over something like this will not happen again.

column2: why am i sharing this with you guys? i want you to know that being brave and being vulnerable but the people you are close with is liberating. i can't remember a time where i was open and honest about my feelings
column4: where i had a negative reaction. it is tough to share emotions and to share shortcomings
column5: but it is so worth it in the end.

column1: how can we all be brave today? is there a time where you have shared your vulnerability with others and it's just been a weight lifted off your shoulders?

column1: 266930;instagram;2018-10-30 16:30:39;FALSE;"if had to give the word 'blessing' a synonym
column2: my mind won't give a second thought

column1: she; she is not beautiful with a fairy white face
column2: she has high pigmentation of melanin (dark complexion) and there is a mole on the right of her chin and a cut right on her forehead. but
column3: she has her own charm. she carries her flaws like a crown and walks like a queen. her hair falls straight to her shoulder and makes a cute face when she ties it while making a bun. she would laugh furiously making one embarrass and cry sliently behind closed doors.

column1: she's a bibliophile but knows how to read between the lines
column2: she won't know that i don't like pineapple on my pizza
column3: but she takes atmost care that my past should not hover over my present. she wears my dreams on her eyes and makes me remind of it with every blink. she won't join me at club but will always hold my hand when i am fighting with my responsibilities. she blabbers my achievements to the world and hides my secret like a treasure. she writes poetry when she is sad and bombards her p.js when i am off. she dances with me like no one is watching but pays careful attention on my each step i take towards life.

column1: she is a half written poetry
column2: an epilogue of my happiness and a story within herself.
all the gifts god has gifted me. she is the one i love the most.

column3: but she takes atmost care that my past should not hover over my present. she wears my dreams on her eyes and makes me remind of it with every blink. she will not join me at club but will always hold my hand when i am fighting with my responsibilities. she blabbers my achievements to the world and hides my secret like a treasure. she writes poetry when she is sad and bombards her p.js when i am off. she dances with me like no one is watching but pays careful attention on my each step i take towards life.

column2: an epilogue of my happiness and a story within herself.
all the gifts god has gifted me. she is the one i love the most.
